to the editor those simple science fairs go the way of the dinosaurs front page april 30 alerts us to demeaning science fair judges and to students who worry that if their nervousness is visible their project 's rating will suffer what phd candidate has not been nervous facing a thesis defense what law student does not sweat nervously approaching the bar exam as a science fair judge i saw work as well done as that presented to me when i was a medical school professor as well as projects at the other end of the spectrum my colleagues and i understood that our task was to stimulate a love for learning not a disrespect for teachers laughing at a student for a science project with such adults setting the example it is n't surprising that our students are sliding down the curve of international excellence thomas w filardo cincinnati april 30 2003

